## The Resulting Simple Interface

After configuring as **Standalone** with these settings, your BRAM will have exactly what you need:

```verilog
your_coeff_rom your_bram_inst (
    .clka(clk),        // Clock input
    .addra(addr),      // Address input (selects which coefficient)
    .douta(coeff)      // ⭐ 16-bit coefficient output!
    // No ena, no wea, no rsta, no rsta_busy - clean and simple!
);
```

## Why "Standalone" = "Native"

The search results confirm this :
- **Standalone mode** = Native interface = Direct control from your logic
- **BRAM Controller mode** = AXI interface = Needs an external controller

So you're all set! **Select "Standalone"** and you'll get the simple interface with `clka`, `addra`, and `douta` signals that you need for your coefficient ROM.
